{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We further evaluate on the SUPERB [24], which is designed to provide a standard and comprehensive testbed for pre-trained speech models on various speech tasks.",
    "Experimental SetupAll pre-training experiments are conducted using fairseq toolkit [25].",
    "For GAN-based tokenizer, we mainly follow the training process and hyper-parameters in [16].",
    "Specifically, we first use the unsupervised voice activity detection [26] to remove the silences from speech and then feed the speech into the pre-trained speech model, i.e., wav2vec 2.0-large 2, to extract high-level speech representations.",
    "For unpaired text, we convert the word sequences into phoneme sequences using an off-the-shelf phonemizer [27], which contains a total of 41 monophones, including a silence symbol."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
